The commit message mentions removing tests related to READ_ONLY_THP_FOR_FS.
However, removing the LOCAL_FILE_BACKED fixture variant completely prevents
the kselftest harness from running any test in the entire suite against
local file mappings.

Does this unintentionally drop test coverage for basic guard region
operations (fork, mprotect, split/merge, etc.) on regular files?

If the removal of file-backed testing was truly intentional, does this
leave unused harness state and dead code behind?

For example, is_anon_backed() now always returns true since it only checks
ANON_BACKED and SHMEM_BACKED. Any code checking !is_anon_backed(variant)
is now unreachable.

Additionally, self->path is no longer populated with a real file path
by open_file(), which makes the teardown logic unlink(self->path)
permanently dead code.

